ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Not as much contact as should have had
Could have been kinder, more considerate
Care relieves me of worry, uncertainty

Notes: TotScore = ptst(Q1 + Q2 + Q3 + Q4 + Q5 + Q6 + Q7 + Q8 + Q9 + Q10 + Q11 + Q12 + Q13)

ElementDescription: Study; The code for each individual study
Notes: e.g., the name of the study in multi-grant collections
N1=Non-Responder Entering Fluvoxamine; N2=Non-Responder Entering Fluoxetine; R1=Maintenance; R2=Responder Entering Fluvoxamine; R3=Responder Entering Fluoxetine

ElementDescription: Compared to how you felt at the very beginning of the study, how would you rate your improvement
Notes: 0 = Not assessed;   1 = Very much improved;   2 = Much improved;   3 = Minimally improved;   4 = No Change;   5 = Minimally worse;   6 = Much worse;   7 = Very much worse

ElementDescription: Which study tablet do you think you received
Notes: 0= Not assessed; 1= Active (Sulforphane, Probiotic, Synbiotic); 2= Placebo; 3= Probiotic

ElementDescription: How would you rate the overall improvement of this client during the time you saw them?
How helpful were you to this client?
How would you rate your own satisfaction level concerning your therapy with this client?
How would you rate the amount of support that you have felt from other therapists in your treatment of this client?
What types of things have made you feel supported or unsupported? (e.g., ideas from consultation or supervision, hearing other''s issues, everyone else struggling too)
Knowing what you know now, how likely would you choose this treatment in the future for a client comparable to this client?

Notes: Sum of items csat_1-csat_4 and item csat_6 re-coded to a 1-5 scale
